  <sect2 role="package">
    <title>Introduction to MelonDS</title>

    <para>
      The MelonDS package provides an NDS emulator.
    </para>

    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Download (HTTP): <ulink url="&melonds-download-http;"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect3">melonds Dependencies</bridgehead>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Required</bridgehead>
    <para role="required">
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/general/cmake.html">CMake</ulink>,
      <xref linkend="enet"/>,
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/kde/extra-cmake-modules.html">extra-cmake-modules</ulink>,
      <xref linkend="faad2"/>,
      &unzip;,
      &opengl;,
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/x/qt6.html">Qt-6</ulink>,
      &sdl2;, and
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/x/x7lib.html">Xorg Libraries</ulink>
    </para>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Recommended</bridgehead>
    <para role="recommended">
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/x/hicolor-icon-theme.html">hicolor-icon-theme</ulink>
    </para>

  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of MelonDS</title>

    <para>
      Install MelonDS by running the following
      commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>mkdir build &amp;&amp;
cd    build &amp;&amp;

cmake -D CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr   \
      -D CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release    \
      -G Ninja .. &amp;&amp;

ninja</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now, as the &root; user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>ninja install</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

